# Notes on Requirement Coverage

These use cases intentionally group related functional requirements into user-centered workflows. Not every functional requirement needs its own separate use case. For example, data storage, access control, and notification requirements are usually referenced inside the workflows they support rather than written as separate actor-driven use cases.
